Text.Value: She caught you with Nibbles - that was his name. Forced you to get rid of him... in front of everyone as an example. You always loved animals, but you never let yourself get too close after that.
Not at all - if anything, they seemed pleased your training was paying off.
I never saw the Mother Superior smile very often, but she did then. I think she was proud of you.
Shadowheart - I mean, my lady. I'm sorry... that takes some getting used to.
She caught you with him. Forced you to get rid of him... in front of everyone to make an example.
This is not the time for talk.
Yes. I had been wondering about that.
I think it was six against two, and most of them were bigger than us, to boot. But you saw them off, all of them.
A collision between your elbow and the teeth of a girl called Buddug - she came away from it worse than you.
I don't suppose there are any pleasant memories you could share?
Please - don't call me 'friend'. You know what it's like here - backstabbing, vying for favour.
At least we can talk freely, now that she is gone. What can I do for you?
It could be dangerous for me, if others think I'm your favourite.
From what you said before, you're the one responsible for my hair?
Hidden at the back of the storage area. Luckily enough, as quartermaster, I was able to keep it hidden back there. It should be, well, if not how you remember it, exactly as you left it.
Nibbles. I suggested Brie, but you were having none of it.
Any time.
Just small things, silly things... the sort you'd scarcely recall even if your memories were left intact.
No need for such formality - we're friends.
Remains to be seen. This place is all I've ever known. In time, perhaps I'll venture out there, see what I've been missing. But for now... old habits die hard.
You'd be the first. As quartermaster, I was able to keep it hidden back there, exactly as you left it.
I can still scarcely believe it. You've returned, and the Mother Superior is gone... So much can change, so quickly...
The plait and fringe? Yes - on your instructions, of course. You were very intent on a bold look, I think you said. My hands were cramped by the time I finished, but you were very pleased.
Shadowheart, good to see you again.
What do you seek?
Be sure to get everything you need. Come tomorrow, I'll be gone.
What happened to him?
In any case, the Mother Superior soon broke up the fighting, though she didn't punish us. In fact, I saw her smiling - I think she was proud of you.
As for the scar, that was from a collision between your elbow and the teeth of a girl called Buddug. She was on the same mission as you. I suppose she won't be coming back...
There's much I still can't remember... Can you share anything with me? From when we were young?
Anything else?
Shadowheart. Do you need supplies? Or just wanted to talk, perhaps?
Leave.
You always loved animals, but you never let yourself get too close after that.
Leave me be.
I'm sorry. Not the sort of thing you want to hear, I'm sure.
I think I found the place you mean - behind a storage area.
There were some bruised lips and black eyes in the mess hall that night. From then on, they left us alone. Or at least, they bothered us less.
So, my hair... that was you?
My lady. How may I serve you?
Well... you had a pet mouse for a while. It was against the rules, of course. You used to hide him under your robes and feed him from your rations.
I like the new look as well, though. You always did like a dramatic touch.

EditorData.NodeContext: Playful/smiling (SH's hair changed after she rejected her goddess)

Text.Value: I was there when you picked that up - it was years ago, when we were initiates. Some of the others were intent on tormenting us... until you showed them the error of their ways.
We weren't punished for fighting?
You had a little hiding place that you went to when you needed to get away - you brought me there sometimes. We'd talk, play, read, do each other's hair...
Go on...
Are you just going to remain here? There's no need - Viconia is gone.
Greetings. Do you seek to trade? As Shadowheart's friend, I'll extend the privilege to you as well.
You know about that? It's barely the size of a pea.
Did he have a name?
She was on the same mission as you. I suppose she won't be coming back...
A hiding place? Where is it?
Shadowheart. Do you need supplies? Or just wanted to talk, perhaps?
Let me see your wares.
You mentioned I had a hideout in here somewhere - where?
Shadowheart. Do you need supplies? Or just wanted to talk, perhaps?
What about the scar?
Well... you know that little scar on your elbow?

Synopsis: An old friend from Shadowheart involved in the Shar Cult. Will appear like a one node NPC to other players if her default dialog is not unlocked. Can offer trade.
